    <Group name="orbit_info">
        <Dimension name="crossing_time" size="444"/>
        <Dimension name="sc_orient_time" size="1"/>
        <Float64 name="crossing_time">
            <Dim name="/orbit_info/crossing_time"/>
            <Attribute name="long_name" type="String">
                <Value>Ascending Node Crossing Time</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="standard_name" type="String">
                <Value>time</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="units" type="String">
                <Value>seconds since 2018-01-01</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="source" type="String">
                <Value>POD/PPD</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="contentType" type="String">
                <Value>referenceInformation</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="description" type="String">
                <Value>The time, in seconds since the ATLAS SDP GPS Epoch, at which the ascending node crosses the equator. The ATLAS Standard Data Products (SDP) epoch offset is defined within /ancillary_data/atlas_sdp_gps_epoch as the number of GPS seconds between the GPS epoch (1980-01-06T00:00:00.000000Z UTC) and the ATLAS SDP epoch. By adding the offset contained within atlas_sdp_gps_epoch to delta time parameters, the time in gps_seconds relative to the GPS epoch can be computed.</Value>
            </Attribute>
        </Float64>
        <Float64 name="sc_orient_time">
            <Dim name="/orbit_info/sc_orient_time"/>
            <Attribute name="long_name" type="String">
                <Value>Time of Last Spacecraft Orientation Change</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="standard_name" type="String">
                <Value>time</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="units" type="String">
                <Value>seconds since 2018-01-01</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="source" type="String">
                <Value>POD/PPD</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="contentType" type="String">
                <Value>referenceInformation</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="description" type="String">
                <Value>The time of the last spacecraft orientation change between forward, backward and transitional flight modes, expressed in seconds since the ATLAS SDP GPS Epoch. ICESat-2 is considered to be flying forward when the weak beams are leading the strong beams; and backward when the strong beams are leading the weak beams. ICESat-2 is considered to be in transition while it is maneuvering between the two orientations. Science quality is potentially degraded while in transition mode. The ATLAS Standard Data Products (SDP) epoch offset is defined within /ancillary_data/atlas_sdp_gps_epoch as the number of GPS seconds between the GPS epoch (1980-01-06T00:00:00.000000Z UTC) and the ATLAS SDP epoch. By adding the offset contained within atlas_sdp_gps_epoch to delta time parameters, the time in gps_seconds relative to the GPS epoch can be computed.</Value>
            </Attribute>
        </Float64>
        <UInt16 name="orbit_number">
            <Dim name="/orbit_info/crossing_time"/>
            <Attribute name="long_name" type="String">
                <Value>Orbit Number</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="units" type="String">
                <Value>1</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="source" type="String">
                <Value>Operations</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="valid_min" type="UInt16">
                <Value>1</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="valid_max" type="UInt16">
                <Value>65000</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="contentType" type="String">
                <Value>referenceInformation</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="description" type="String">
                <Value>Unique identifying number for each planned ICESat-2 orbit.</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="coordinates" type="String">
                <Value>crossing_time</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Map name="/orbit_info/crossing_time"/>
        </UInt16>
        <Float64 name="lan">
            <Dim name="/orbit_info/crossing_time"/>
            <Attribute name="long_name" type="String">
                <Value>Ascending Node Longitude</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="units" type="String">
                <Value>degrees_east</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="source" type="String">
                <Value>POD/PPD</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="valid_min" type="Float64">
                <Value>-180.</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="valid_max" type="Float64">
                <Value>180.</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="contentType" type="String">
                <Value>referenceInformation</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="description" type="String">
                <Value>Longitude at the ascending node crossing.</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="coordinates" type="String">
                <Value>crossing_time</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Map name="/orbit_info/crossing_time"/>
        </Float64>
        <Int8 name="sc_orient">
            <Dim name="/orbit_info/sc_orient_time"/>
            <Attribute name="long_name" type="String">
                <Value>Spacecraft Orientation</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="units" type="String">
                <Value>1</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="source" type="String">
                <Value>POD/PPD</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="valid_min" type="Int8">
                <Value>0</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="valid_max" type="Int8">
                <Value>2</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="contentType" type="String">
                <Value>referenceInformation</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="description" type="String">
                <Value>This parameter tracks the spacecraft orientation between forward, backward and transitional flight modes. ICESat-2 is considered to be flying forward when the weak beams are leading the strong beams; and backward when the strong beams are leading the weak beams. ICESat-2 is considered to be in transition while it is maneuvering between the two orientations. Science quality is potentially degraded while in transition mode.</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="coordinates" type="String">
                <Value>sc_orient_time</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="flag_meanings" type="String">
                <Value>backward forward transition</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="flag_values" type="Int8">
                <Value>0</Value>
                <Value>1</Value>
                <Value>2</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Map name="/orbit_info/sc_orient_time"/>
        </Int8>
        <Int16 name="rgt">
            <Dim name="/orbit_info/crossing_time"/>
            <Attribute name="long_name" type="String">
                <Value>Reference Ground track</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="units" type="String">
                <Value>1</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="source" type="String">
                <Value>POD/PPD</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="valid_min" type="Int16">
                <Value>1</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="valid_max" type="Int16">
                <Value>1387</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="contentType" type="String">
                <Value>referenceInformation</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="description" type="String">
                <Value>The reference ground track (RGT) is the track on the earth at which a specified unit vector within the observatory is pointed. Under nominal operating conditions, there will be no data collected along the RGT, as the RGT is spanned by GT3 and GT4.  During slews or off-pointing, it is possible that ground tracks may intersect the RGT. The ICESat-2 mission has 1387 RGTs.</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="coordinates" type="String">
                <Value>crossing_time</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Map name="/orbit_info/crossing_time"/>
        </Int16>
        <Int8 name="cycle_number">
            <Dim name="/orbit_info/crossing_time"/>
            <Attribute name="long_name" type="String">
                <Value>Cycle Number</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="units" type="String">
                <Value>1</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="valid_min" type="Int8">
                <Value>0</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="valid_max" type="Int8">
                <Value>50</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="contentType" type="String">
                <Value>referenceInformation</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="description" type="String">
                <Value>A count of the number of exact repeats of this reference orbit.</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="coordinates" type="String">
                <Value>crossing_time</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute name="source" type="String">
                <Value>Operations</Value>
            </Attribute>
            <Map name="/orbit_info/crossing_time"/>
        </Int8>
        <Attribute name="Description" type="String">
            <Value>Contains orbit information.</Value>
        </Attribute>
        <Attribute name="data_rate" type="String">
            <Value>Varies. Data are only provided when one of the stored values (besides time) changes.</Value>
        </Attribute>
